Project Title: Hospital Management System (SQL)

Description:
This project involves the design and implementation of a relational database system to manage hospital operations. It models real-world entities such as hospitals, doctors, patients, appointments, departments, and prescriptions.

Key Features:

* Fully normalized relational schema
* Use of primary and foreign keys for integrity
* Complex SQL queries including joins, aggregations, and window functions
* Realistic dataset for simulation

Technical Highlights:

* Implementation of multi-table relationships
* Analytical queries using DENSE_RANK and subqueries
* Use of CASE statements for classification
* Time-based analysis using date functions

Outcome:
The system enables efficient storage, retrieval, and analysis of hospital data. It demonstrates strong SQL proficiency and problem-solving ability.

Conclusion:
This project showcases practical database design skills and advanced SQL techniques applicable in real-world data systems and analytics roles.
